This post generated a much needed debate on the ethics of using such technologies on animals to benefit humans. Are we being yield-obsessed instead of being kind to animals? Even if it made the cows less stressed, is it ok to use VR on cows?

Because there is not a single industry from entertainment to law to manufacturing that won't use AI to serve its clients better. And you don't want to miss out on that revolution.

üë©üèΩ‚ÄçüíªTo feel confident in giving our perspective, to demand the right to participate, we must upskill ourselves first. Every girl should learn the basics of AI no matter her age, passion, or occupation. 

Why?

Don't be invisible. 

Girls feel invisible when they sit in meetings and they don't understand the tech, data and AI lingo being thrown at them. 

We feel invisible when instead of asking us for our opinion on a product built using data or AI, our male colleague is asked.
